      "message": "In clamping mode the color of any pixel beyond width (or height) is just the color of the pixel at (width - 1) (remember there is no pixel at width because that is outside sampling space. Since we sample it pixel centers, the coordinate of the pixel is not (width - 1), but (width - 1 + .5). The .5 also makes it so that bilerp samples that pixel perfectly for points off the sample space, but I don\u0027 think that matters here.",
