      "writtenOn": "2017-01-20T15:50:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I believe the big difference is that sampling a gradient at 1.0 does not result in an asan failure (reading outside the bitmap) while sampling a bitmap would. While the gradient would have higher fidelity to the drawing command, it does not result in dangerous behavior. Therefore, it is a judgment call as to whether the extra speed is worth the fidelity, where with image sampling it is not. The need to clamp on [0, limit) was very rare, and I had to work with images for months to run into the situation.",
